Duodenal CD8+ T resident memory cell apoptosis contributes to gut barrier dysfunction and microbial translocation in early alcohol-associated liver disease in humans.
Duodenal CD8+ TRM apoptosis related to functional changes in lysosomes and lipid metabolism points to impaired gut adaptive immunity specifically in patients with AUD who developed early ALD.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Earnings during adulthood in patients with childhood-onset inflammatory bowel disease: A nationwide population-based cohort study.
Overall, the negative influence of disease on earnings in early adult age was modest for patients with childhood-onset IBD. The markedly larger negative income gap from ages 20 to 30 in patients with more severe IBD during childhood should be recognised.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Therapeutic management and outcomes in inflammatory bowel diseases, 2010 to 2017 in cohorts from Denmark, Sweden and Norway.
 Between 2010 and 2017, surgery rates among Scandinavian patients with IBD remained stable, with no clear changes in hospitalisation rates despite the increasing use of immunomodulators and biologics.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Tolerance to sterilised cow's milk in patients with eosinophilic oesophagitis triggered by milk.
 Sterilised milk did not trigger EoE in two-thirds of patients with documented milk-induced EoE, either in the short term or in the long term.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Am J Gastroenterol
    Cardiovascular mapping in cirrhosis from the compensated stage to hepatorenal syndrome: a magnetic resonance study: Hemodynamic changes with progression of cirrhosis.
 The regional cardiocirculatory changes appear closely linked to clinical symptoms with three distinguished hemodynamic stages from compensated to decompensated cirrhosis and finally to HRS-AKI. The attenuated renal perfusion despite high CO in HRS-AKI patients challenges the prevailing pathophysiological hypothesis of cardiac dysfunction as a causal factor in HRS-AKI. Finally, MRI seems an accurate and reliable non-invasive method to assess hemodynamics and has potential as a diagnostic tool in patients with cirrhosis.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Heterogeneity in Center Practices in Liver Transplantation for Alcohol-associated Liver Disease in the United States.
Our findings highlight a change in center attitudes towards LT for ALD, particularly for severe AAH.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Endoscopy
    Performance measures for colonoscopy in inflammatory bowel disease patients: European Society of Gastrointestinal Endoscopy (ESGE) Quality Improvement Initiative.
Therefore, our aim was to provide endoscopy services across Europe and other interested countries with a tool for quality monitoring and improvement in IBD colonoscopy. Eight key performance measures and one minor performance measure were recommended for measurement and evaluation in daily endoscopy practice.
